Package com.gmail.aydinov.sergey.simple_debugger_plugin.processor

Interface UiEventCollector

All Known Implementing Classes:
SimpleDebuggerEventQueue
public interface UiEventCollector
Interface for collecting UI events produced by the user interface. Implementations typically store events in a queue for later processing by worker threads.

Author: Sergei Aidinov
Email: sergey.aydinov@gmail.com

    • pollUiEvent

      AbstractUIEvent pollUiEvent() throws InterruptedException
      Retrieves and removes the next UI event from the queue. If the queue is empty, this method may return null or wait, depending on implementation.
      Returns:
      the next UI event, or null if none is available
      Throws:
      InterruptedException - if the operation is interrupted while waiting
